had to happen in certain ways for any of us to exist. From an extremely improbable asteroid impact, to the wild gyrations of the Ice Age, to invisible accidents in our parents' gonads, we are all here through an astonishing series of fortunate events. And chance continues to reign every day over the razor-thin line between our life and death.This is a relatively small book about a really big idea. It is also a spirited tale. Drawing inspiration from Monty Python, Kurt Vonnegut, and other great thinkers, and crafted by one of today's most accomplished science storytellers, A Series of Fortunate Events is an irresistibly entertaining and thought-provoking account of one of the most important but least appreciated facts of life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aEvolution (Biology)xHistory. 0aLifexOrigin. 0aLife. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Evolution.2bisacsh  aA Series of Unfortunate Events.  aColbert.  aEric Idle.  aEvolution.  aFlying Circus.  aGervais.  aGraham Chapman.  aIzzard.  aJohn Cleese.  aLemony Snicket.  aMaher.  aMichael Palin.  aMonty Python and the Holy Grail.  aMonty Python's Life of Brian.  aSecret Policeman's Ball.  aSilvermain.  aStephen Colbert.  aTerry Gilliam.  aTerry Jones.  abiology.  acancer.  aclimate.  aearth.  agenes.  aluck.  amutation.  arandom.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070480808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2020z9783110704600oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPri